# While and Do-While

**While loop** – checks condition first, then executes.
```dart
while (condition) {
  // code
}
```

**Do-while loop** – executes at least once, then checks condition.
```dart
do {
  // code
} while (condition);
```

Use while when you want to repeat zero or more times. Use do-while when you want at least one execution.

quizData.question:
How many times does the body of this loop run?
```dart
int x = 10;
do {
  print(x);
  x++;
} while (x < 10);
```

slides.codeSnippet:
void main() {
  int i = 0;
  while (i < 0) {
    print('while: $i'); // never runs
    i++;
  }

  int j = 0;
  do {
    print('do-while: $j'); // runs once
    j++;
  } while (j < 0);
}
